WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:16.360 --> 00:18.362
(BIRDS SINGING)

00:21.800 --> 00:23.165
(GRUNTS)

00:25.400 --> 00:27.402
Oh!

00:40.720 --> 00:42.722
(WHISTLES)

00:49.520 --> 00:51.522
(GRUNTS)

00:59.360 --> 01:01.362
(SIGHS THEN GIGGLING)

01:14.000 --> 01:21.168
INSTRUCTIONS NOT INCLUDED

01:21.320 --> 01:23.641
(SEAGULLS SQUAWKING)

01:23.800 --> 01:25.689
MAN: <i>My Dad
used to say that fear...</i>

01:25.840 --> 01:29.845
<i>...is like the creatures in nature
that man can tame.</i>

01:30.600 --> 01:32.682
A creature?
Like which one?

01:33.160 --> 01:34.286
Like...

01:34.520 --> 01:35.681
...like a wolf.

01:36.360 --> 01:38.806
- Why a wolf?
- Because if a wolf...

01:39.200 --> 01:41.851
...sees you're scared,
it will attack you.

01:42.360 --> 01:44.169
You have to stare back at it...

01:44.640 --> 01:48.326
...to learn how to tame it,
to scare it away.

01:48.480 --> 01:53.566
- Sha! Sha!
- Sha! Sha!

01:53.720 --> 01:55.768
Sha. Sha. Sha.

01:56.960 --> 02:00.521
<i>He'd also say there were
big fears and small fears.</i>

02:00.720 --> 02:03.007
JOHNNY:
Hold on, son. Everything's okay.

02:03.360 --> 02:06.728
That's why I named you Valentin.
Because you're so brave.

02:06.880 --> 02:08.370
(LAUGHING)

02:08.560 --> 02:10.562
(WHIMPERING)

02:11.000 --> 02:12.889
VALENTIN:
Dad, please, let me out of here! Dad!

02:13.040 --> 02:15.964
<i>My Dad not only prepared
me for this world's fears.</i>

02:16.360 --> 02:19.807
Hold on, kiddo.
It's almost midnight.

02:19.960 --> 02:23.248
Tame the fear son.
Everything's okay.

02:23.520 --> 02:25.761
Remember... Sha, sha.

02:25.920 --> 02:27.081
VALENTIN: Sha! Sha!

02:27.240 --> 02:30.084
<i>He also prepared me for
the fears of the afterlife.</i>

02:30.240 --> 02:33.164
Please, Dad!
Let me out, Dad!

02:33.360 --> 02:35.362
(GROWLING)

02:37.000 --> 02:38.650
Sha.

02:40.480 --> 02:43.290
Come here.
You're so brave, son!

02:43.480 --> 02:46.165
Congratulations!
What happened?

02:46.600 --> 02:49.285
- Did you pee yourself?
- No, it wasn't me.

02:49.520 --> 02:53.002
- It was the wolf.
- What wolf? You're crazy.

02:53.240 --> 02:55.447
- Let's go home.
- No, let go of me!

02:55.680 --> 02:57.728
- I don't love you anymore!
- But I do!

02:57.920 --> 03:00.571
Come on, let's go
find some ghosts! Run!

03:00.760 --> 03:02.728
<i>Even though, honestly...</i>

03:03.600 --> 03:06.080
<i>...I was never able
to master the small fears...</i>

03:06.240 --> 03:08.049
Don't throw me
in the water, Dad!

03:08.280 --> 03:10.320
- <i>...or the medium ones...</i>
- It's for your own good!

03:10.440 --> 03:13.091
If you do this,
you'll never be scared again...

03:13.280 --> 03:15.169
- ...or the big ones.
<i>- Dad!</i>

03:15.440 --> 03:17.408
25 YEARS LATER

03:18.240 --> 03:19.810
Unh. Kiss me.

03:22.120 --> 03:24.282
<i>But if I couldn't master
the big fears...</i>

03:24.960 --> 03:27.440
<i>...the medium fears
and the small fears...</i>

03:30.640 --> 03:32.722
I love it when
you grab my hand.

03:32.960 --> 03:36.123
<i>...let alone the mother
of all fears:</i>

03:36.720 --> 03:37.960
Valentin...

03:38.640 --> 03:40.529
...marry me!

03:40.880 --> 03:42.325
<i>Commitment!</i>

03:46.320 --> 03:47.446
Valentin!

04:33.200 --> 04:34.531
- Valentin...
- Hm?

04:34.680 --> 04:36.091
...do you love me?

04:36.680 --> 04:38.364
- Mm-hm.
- Why?

04:39.680 --> 04:41.444
I love you because...

04:42.200 --> 04:44.123
...because you're different.

04:45.040 --> 04:47.202
Because you're... different.

04:48.200 --> 04:50.567
Because you're different.

04:51.080 --> 04:52.525
Because you're different!

05:13.040 --> 05:14.724
(IN ENGLISH)
Do you love me?

05:15.720 --> 05:17.370
I adore you, Julie.

05:17.720 --> 05:20.200
You're my first and last love.

05:32.560 --> 05:35.211
20 MONTHS LATER...

05:44.520 --> 05:46.921
Can you just hang on a second, okay?

05:52.720 --> 05:54.722
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

06:11.200 --> 06:12.201
Valentin.

06:12.360 --> 06:13.361
Yes?

06:13.960 --> 06:15.291
Have we met?

06:16.480 --> 06:19.051
I... I was your endless love.

06:19.200 --> 06:20.281
What?

06:21.160 --> 06:25.484
(IN SPANISH) I was your eternal love
a year and a half ago.

06:26.320 --> 06:28.687
Oh, yeah! Right!

06:29.800 --> 06:32.201
- Is that your baby?
- Yes.

06:32.600 --> 06:34.090
Did you get married?

06:34.960 --> 06:38.009
No, you idiot!
She's your daughter.

06:39.320 --> 06:41.243
VALENTIN:
No. Hold on a minute!

06:41.480 --> 06:43.403
I don't want to have children.

06:43.680 --> 06:46.160
I don't want troubles, and that
baby doesn't even look like me...

06:46.320 --> 06:48.004
Do you have ten dollars?

06:48.440 --> 06:51.091
- What?
- Ten dollars, to pay the cab.

06:51.720 --> 06:54.963
No, I don't have dollars.
Let me see...

07:02.920 --> 07:04.922
(IN ENGLISH)
Hold on.

07:16.000 --> 07:17.684
(COOING)

07:20.520 --> 07:23.649
Ch-ch-ch-ch! Stop that!
That's not your food.

07:25.440 --> 07:30.048
I don't think your sister
is coming back for the baby.

07:30.600 --> 07:32.568
The truth is...

07:33.080 --> 07:34.525
...it looks like...

07:36.080 --> 07:38.128
...I'm the baby's father.

07:38.640 --> 07:40.881
You did it with your sister?

07:41.480 --> 07:42.891
No! No, no!

07:43.040 --> 07:45.486
No, it's just that...
Well... she's not my sister.

07:45.760 --> 07:48.411
But she did go to pay
the cab, though.

07:50.640 --> 07:51.766
Well...

07:52.320 --> 07:54.448
- Here!
- What?

07:54.600 --> 07:55.647
What?

07:55.800 --> 07:59.691
I just remembered
I have to go to the doctor.

08:00.160 --> 08:03.323
Yes, I have a problem with
my... prostate.

08:03.480 --> 08:04.925
Yes. Bye, honey.

08:05.280 --> 08:07.442
Women don't have prostates.

08:07.760 --> 08:08.841
No?

08:09.520 --> 08:12.922
Well, that's why I have
to see a doctor. Bye.

08:13.120 --> 08:16.761
Hey, but... you said you'd stay
the whole weekend!

08:32.640 --> 08:34.607
Hey, you know your mom.

08:34.799 --> 08:37.167
She wouldn't leave you
here, would she?

08:37.799 --> 08:39.131
Would she?

08:39.760 --> 08:41.922
(PHONE RINGING)

08:44.840 --> 08:45.966
Hello?

08:47.080 --> 08:49.447
Hi, it's me. Julie.

08:49.600 --> 08:51.648
What Julie?
Oh, Julie!

08:51.840 --> 08:52.841
(SIGHS)

08:53.000 --> 08:56.322
Look, I'm... I'm sorry.

08:58.640 --> 09:01.120
(VOICE BREAKING) Please take
good care of her. She's just a baby.

09:01.280 --> 09:03.726
<i>- Julie, where are you?</i>
- I...

09:03.960 --> 09:06.201
<i>- Julie!</i>
- I can't.

09:06.360 --> 09:07.441
(IN SPANISH)
I can't do it.

09:08.240 --> 09:09.287
(IN ENGLISH)
I'm sorry.

09:09.480 --> 09:11.244
<i>...what is it you can't do?</i>

09:11.440 --> 09:12.566
<i>Julie!</i>

09:13.640 --> 09:15.881
Julie, where are you?
Julie!

09:16.040 --> 09:20.090
<i>WOMAN (OVER PA): Passengers on
Flight 2264 bound for Los Angeles...</i>

09:20.240 --> 09:23.323
<i>...please proceed to Gate 9.</i>

09:24.160 --> 09:25.810
(KEYPAD BEEPS)

09:26.000 --> 09:28.002
I'm such a moron!

09:33.360 --> 09:35.362
(COOING)

09:38.160 --> 09:41.084
The next time I leave you alone
and you don't say anything...

09:41.320 --> 09:43.129
...I swear I'll leave you.

09:55.680 --> 09:57.205
(TIRES SCREECHING)

10:03.120 --> 10:05.088
(HORN HONKING)

10:10.520 --> 10:13.490
AIRPORT

10:23.800 --> 10:26.770
DEPARTURES

10:30.960 --> 10:33.884
Excuse me, ma'am.
Have you seen a blond girl...

10:34.040 --> 10:36.646
...kind of hippy,
in her twenties?

10:40.240 --> 10:42.242
(CHATTERING)

10:53.720 --> 10:55.085
Julie!

10:55.560 --> 10:58.006
Julie! Julie!

11:00.040 --> 11:01.326
Your baby!

11:03.320 --> 11:04.481
Your baby!

11:06.960 --> 11:09.167
Julie!

11:25.000 --> 11:27.401
No, no. It's hard.
It falls down!

11:28.120 --> 11:31.090
- Valentin!
- Can you change diapers, Sammy?

11:31.400 --> 11:34.529
Yeah, sure.
It doesn't have to be disgusting.

11:34.720 --> 11:36.131
It's dirty, but you have to...

11:36.280 --> 11:39.762
...I just go to the bathroom
and wash my hands afterwards.

11:39.920 --> 11:43.447
- Where's Judeisi?
- She's over there. I'll call her.

11:43.800 --> 11:45.040
Judeisi!

11:46.480 --> 11:47.641
What is this?

11:50.240 --> 11:53.005
That's it, my baby.

11:55.600 --> 11:56.806
She's full of crap.

11:57.800 --> 11:59.040
I'll change her diaper.

11:59.800 --> 12:03.122
What's your name?
What's her name, Valentin?

12:03.320 --> 12:04.810
I don't know.

12:05.000 --> 12:07.002
It must be here.

12:07.640 --> 12:08.721
Maggie?

12:09.040 --> 12:12.044
Her name is Maggie.
She's named after a sauce.

12:12.440 --> 12:14.647
- Have some vegetables, kid.
- What are you doing?

12:14.800 --> 12:17.007
I'm giving her carrots.

12:17.560 --> 12:18.891
That's too spicy.

12:20.080 --> 12:23.004
Why don't you just keep her?

12:23.200 --> 12:24.850
It's high time you settled down.

12:25.120 --> 12:27.691
No way!
What would I do with a baby?

12:27.880 --> 12:30.690
Goodbye freedom, goodbye tourists!

12:31.000 --> 12:35.403
What will I do for a living?
I might even have to get a job.

12:36.400 --> 12:39.006
And you'll have
to learn English.

12:39.200 --> 12:42.044
'Cause when she starts talking,
you won't understand her.

12:42.400 --> 12:45.688
I'll have to send her to school,
feed her.

12:45.880 --> 12:48.008
Every day, three times a day.

12:48.400 --> 12:50.687
And speak to her
like a dummy so she'll eat.

12:50.840 --> 12:52.524
(IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE)
Eat, baby! Eat, baby!

12:52.720 --> 12:55.041
(IN NORMAL VOICE) And I'll
have to watch Barney over and over.

12:55.400 --> 12:58.529
One day she'll ask me
why she's growing boobs.

12:58.720 --> 13:00.882
When she's older,
she'll want to borrow my car.

13:01.600 --> 13:05.241
I'll have to beat up her boyfriend
when he knocks her up. No, no!

13:05.760 --> 13:08.127
Besides, I'll suck as a Dad.

13:08.400 --> 13:12.200
Hey, I have an idea!
Write to Angelina Jolie.

13:12.720 --> 13:15.644
Tell her the baby's from
Acapulco or Oaxaca.

13:15.920 --> 13:17.763
Maybe she'll adopt her.

13:18.040 --> 13:20.247
I know!
Let's go to your house.

13:28.040 --> 13:29.929
VALENTIN:
I found this other box.

13:31.080 --> 13:33.845
You must have something
from that Julie woman.

13:34.160 --> 13:35.844
Didn't she leave you a souvenir?

13:37.080 --> 13:38.764
She did.

13:39.160 --> 13:41.208
But I got rid of it with penicillin.

13:41.560 --> 13:46.248
I mean, a telephone number,
an address. Something.

13:46.720 --> 13:49.769
Here's a letter from a Julie.
A Julie.

13:49.960 --> 13:51.041
- Really?
- Yes, look.

13:51.200 --> 13:54.602
- She wrote a letter?
- Didn't you know?

13:55.280 --> 13:57.931
She wrote it a year
and a half ago.

13:58.160 --> 13:59.241
Look!

13:59.480 --> 14:00.561
Let me see!

14:00.960 --> 14:04.282
Does she say how to contact her,
a phone number, anything?

14:04.440 --> 14:05.487
No.

14:06.080 --> 14:08.208
It only says:

14:08.800 --> 14:11.485
"I miss you kissing my..."

14:13.600 --> 14:15.489
How very explicit!

14:16.000 --> 14:19.004
Kisses from L.A.

14:19.200 --> 14:20.770
What does L.A. mean?

14:21.200 --> 14:23.601
Loving American, no?

14:23.840 --> 14:26.605
- Look for her at this hotel.
- What hotel?

14:26.840 --> 14:32.244
This one. Look. California Hills Hotel.
It looks like she works there.

14:32.640 --> 14:34.210
Where is that?

14:36.520 --> 14:40.445
Hey, that's in Los Angeles.
I barely understand English.

14:40.640 --> 14:43.644
I hate the language.
I always flunked it.

14:44.200 --> 14:46.362
Besides, I'm broke.

14:46.640 --> 14:49.291
And you're scared of flying.
Really scared.

14:49.520 --> 14:51.761
You're crazy.
I'm not scared of planes.

14:52.320 --> 14:56.245
Well, then you have no choice
but to keep the baby.

14:57.800 --> 15:00.201
Oh! She's so beautiful.

15:00.840 --> 15:03.844
You'll end up
falling in love with her.

15:18.240 --> 15:21.323
VALENTIN:
<i>I've never been scared of airplanes.</i>

15:22.040 --> 15:23.883
It's just that...

15:24.040 --> 15:27.681
...if we go by road,
we'll save money.

15:27.880 --> 15:30.121
We'll have more time to chat.

15:30.400 --> 15:33.404
We'll have more
father-daughter moments.

15:33.560 --> 15:36.723
Now, if I return you to your mom
it doesn't mean I don't love you.

15:36.880 --> 15:40.009
It's just that you'll be
better off there.

15:40.880 --> 15:45.886
For example, movies premiere
much earlier there.

15:46.080 --> 15:48.890
<i>Just think. When Twilight
premiered here...</i>

15:49.080 --> 15:51.048
<i>...it was already
Breaking Dawn there.</i>

15:51.280 --> 15:53.851
<i>Besides, if you stay here...</i>

15:54.080 --> 15:57.721
<i>you'll be pretty,
but darker and smaller.</i>

15:58.000 --> 15:59.525
<i>But, if you grow up there...</i>

15:59.720 --> 16:03.122
<i>you'll probably
be blond, blue-eyed...</i>

16:03.360 --> 16:04.407
<i>...tall.</i>

16:04.680 --> 16:06.887
<i>Besides, here you could
get mugged any time...</i>

16:07.400 --> 16:09.687
<i>...by a thief or a cop.</i>

16:10.040 --> 16:12.691
<i>Not to mention the corruption...</i>

16:12.880 --> 16:14.041
<i>...drug dealers...</i>

16:14.560 --> 16:15.891
<i>...demonstrations...</i>

16:16.040 --> 16:17.485
<i>...the traffic...</i>

16:18.000 --> 16:19.843
...the politicians...

16:20.200 --> 16:21.884
...potholes...

16:22.200 --> 16:24.202
...the national soccer team.

16:24.560 --> 16:27.370
There are only
disadvantages here.

16:27.560 --> 16:28.925
What?

16:29.920 --> 16:32.161
Are you sleeping again?

16:32.560 --> 16:34.562
But it's time to eat!

16:36.560 --> 16:37.891
Don't you want to eat?

16:38.240 --> 16:41.289
Look.
Your milk is warm now.

16:45.200 --> 16:47.202
(SPITTING)

16:47.840 --> 16:48.921
(GRUNTS)

16:49.080 --> 16:51.560
I want an abortion!

16:52.240 --> 16:54.925
Damn cheap condoms!

17:12.520 --> 17:13.806
(GUN COCKS)

17:14.119 --> 17:16.122
Is the baby real?

17:19.640 --> 17:20.721
Get in!

17:21.119 --> 17:22.565
My name is Lupe.

17:24.720 --> 17:27.246
(MAGGIE CRYING)

17:27.960 --> 17:28.961
VALENTIN:
Enough!

17:30.280 --> 17:31.611
<i>Shh, shh. Enough!</i>

17:31.840 --> 17:32.966
<i>Enough!</i>

17:33.960 --> 17:36.964
<i>I said it's enough!</i>

17:38.840 --> 17:40.649
<i>It's enough!</i>

17:41.480 --> 17:43.642
Can you change diapers?

17:45.360 --> 17:47.567
...I was just asking...

17:47.720 --> 17:49.722
(MAGGIE CONTINUES CRYING)

17:52.320 --> 17:56.484
Oh! Yuck!

17:57.480 --> 17:59.244
Is she sick?

18:00.360 --> 18:01.441
Sorry.

18:02.480 --> 18:04.528
It wasn't her this time.

18:06.720 --> 18:09.405
(MAGGIE CONTINUES CRYING)

18:14.880 --> 18:16.882
Change her already, will you?

18:17.400 --> 18:19.607
I'll change her for a quiet baby.

18:19.880 --> 18:22.690
Don't try to be funny.
Change her!

18:24.040 --> 18:26.202
I'll just finish my burger first.

18:27.720 --> 18:30.041
(TIRES SCREECHING)

18:32.680 --> 18:34.682
Right now!

18:36.920 --> 18:38.410
Good idea.

18:38.720 --> 18:40.051
Right now!

18:51.040 --> 18:52.166
See?

18:52.720 --> 18:55.564
You could've changed her
three hours ago.

18:57.040 --> 18:58.724
(BURPS)

18:59.240 --> 19:00.401
(MAGGIE BURPS)

19:00.560 --> 19:02.562
She sounded just like me!

19:02.720 --> 19:05.451
We're identical, mija!

19:16.480 --> 19:17.641
(HORN BLARES)

19:28.080 --> 19:30.526
VALENTIN:
Look, the baby's a gringa!

19:30.680 --> 19:33.968
I'll just drop her off with her
mom in L.A. and come back.

19:34.920 --> 19:35.921
(SPEAKS IN SPANISH)

19:36.080 --> 19:40.608
Oh... I told you I don't have one,
I didn't know, Mr. Copper.

19:40.760 --> 19:44.924
But I'm not staying. I'll just
drop her off and come right back.

19:45.120 --> 19:46.610
I'll be back today.

19:46.960 --> 19:49.611
You can have my watch
and my ID as proof that...

19:49.760 --> 19:52.604
...I'll be back in 5 hours.

19:53.000 --> 19:54.570
(IN ENGLISH)
Get out.

19:55.200 --> 19:56.486
What?

19:57.280 --> 19:58.611
Didn't he go for it?

19:59.280 --> 20:02.762
Why didn't you tell me
you didn't have a visa?

20:06.480 --> 20:09.131
Are you going
to Los Angeles, too?

20:09.280 --> 20:11.123
ALL:
Shh!

20:20.560 --> 20:22.130
ALL:
Ah...

20:22.320 --> 20:23.401
Water!

20:23.800 --> 20:26.167
Say hello to your Aunt Zenaida.

20:26.320 --> 20:28.004
Careful! Get up.

20:30.520 --> 20:32.488
Say hello to Queta, babe.

20:32.640 --> 20:36.008
Tell her that grandma didn't
even make it to Cuernavaca.

20:36.160 --> 20:37.286
Thank you.

20:37.640 --> 20:38.971
Thank you, Lupe.

20:41.040 --> 20:42.485
Thank you so much.

20:42.640 --> 20:43.766
Lupe...

20:43.920 --> 20:46.969
Do you know where
this hotel is?

20:49.680 --> 20:52.524
(IN ENGLISH) Nah, man.
She doesn't work here anymore.

20:53.000 --> 20:56.129
She... She went down to Mexico
looking for her baby's father.

20:56.680 --> 21:00.480
Then I think she was going to New
York for school or something.

21:00.880 --> 21:03.281
You know what?
She left her phone number here.

21:03.440 --> 21:05.363
You want me to look it up for you?

21:07.680 --> 21:10.604
It's just in the computer back there.
Yeah? Okay.

21:10.760 --> 21:11.761
(SPEAKS IN SPANISH)

21:11.920 --> 21:13.843
I can give it to you.
Just give me one second.

21:14.040 --> 21:15.201
I'll find her.

21:15.360 --> 21:17.806
Whoa, whoa. I'm sorry, but you
can't bring children in here.

21:18.000 --> 21:19.047
What?

21:21.600 --> 21:22.681
No children.

21:22.880 --> 21:24.882
(MAN & WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

21:25.600 --> 21:27.841
But the dog?

21:30.320 --> 21:32.527
No children.

21:32.680 --> 21:33.727
What about the dog?

21:33.880 --> 21:36.645
No children.

21:41.720 --> 21:44.371
Gimme a break.
They let the dog in.

22:25.280 --> 22:26.520
Psst.

22:26.920 --> 22:30.208
Hey, paisana, help me out.
